Extract cell numbers from a Raster object.

Currently only for single layer objects.

cellnumbers(x, query, ...)

Arguments

x

Raster object
query

Spatial object or matrix of coordinates
...

arguments passed on

Value

tbl_df data frame

Examples

library(raster)
r <- raster(volcano)
cr <- cut(r,  pretty(values(r)))
p <- raster::rasterToPolygons(cr, dissolve = TRUE)
#> Loading required namespace: rgeos
tt <- cellnumbers(cr, p)
#> Warning: projections not the same 
#>     x: NA
#> query: NA
library(dplyr)
tt %>% mutate(v = extract(r, cell_)) %>%
group_by(object_) %>%
summarize(mean(v)) %>% mutate(head(pretty(values(r)), -1))
#> # A tibble: 6 x 3
#>   object_ `mean(v)` `head(pretty(values(r)), -1)`
#>     <chr>     <dbl>                         <int>
#> 1       1  97.38693                            80
#> 2       2 110.20931                           100
#> 3       3 130.40073                           120
#> 4       4 149.72827                           140
#> 5       5 170.44589                           160
#> 6       6 186.32022                           180
